  "metadata": {
    "role": "article",
    "roleHeading": "Article",
    "title": "Making changes to reduce memory use"
  },
  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "Overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Once you’ve localized the growth in your app’s memory use to a specific feature or",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "action, you can make changes to reduce memory use. Common causes of excessive memory",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "use and the actions you can take to reduce their impact are described below.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Optimize-image-assets",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Optimize image assets",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Large images, especially at high color depths, use a lot of memory. Optimize assets",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "bundled with the app for the size at which the app displays them. Transform images",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "loaded from other sources—for example, from network services or the user’s photo",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "library—to an appropriate scale and color depth. Use ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/ImageIO",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "for these transforms to minimize memory impact. WWDC 2018 Session 416, ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2018/416",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ", gives advice on",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "choosing appropriate Image I/O transforms.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Reduce-the-size-of-Core-Data-transactions",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Reduce the size of Core Data transactions",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/CoreData",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " stores changes to ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/CoreData/NSManagedObject",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "instances in memory until their associated ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/CoreData/NSManagedObjectContext",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "is saved, at which time it writes changes to the parent ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "NSManagedObjectContext",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "or to the persistent store. Until the changes make their way into the persistent",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "store, they’re resident in memory, so the longer your app goes between saves, the",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "bigger Core Data’s working set can grow. Conversely, the more frequently your app",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "saves, the more writes it makes to the device’s solid-state drive, which impacts",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "performance and increases wear on the drive. Design your app’s persistence model",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "to strike a balance between these two resource constraints.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Discard-unused-view-objects",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Discard unused view objects",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The user isn’t looking at your app’s views when they lock the screen or when the",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "app is in the background. There’s no need to keep images, video, SceneKit scenes,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "and other view-related objects in memory during those times. Release view-related",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "content when your app enters the background, and prepare views again when it re-enters",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "the foreground. For information about preparing your app for background use, see",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/UIKit/managing-your-app-s-life-cycle",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Eliminate-memory-leaks",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Eliminate memory leaks",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "A memory leak occurs when allocated memory becomes unreachable and the app can’t",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "deallocate it. Allowing an allocated-memory pointer to go out of scope without freeing",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "the memory can cause a memory leak. A retain cycle in your app’s object graph can",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "also cause a memory leak. When the app removes its reference to any of the objects",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "in a retain cycle, strong references remain within the cycle, and the objects aren’t",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "released.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Use the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "https://help.apple.com/instruments/mac/10.0/#/dev022f987b",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "to detect memory leaks. Instruments periodically scans the memory your app is using",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "to report allocated but unreachable regions of memory. The Leaks instrument shows",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "the address and size of the leaked memory, along with a stack trace showing the code",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "responsible for allocating the memory.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Remove-references-to-unused-objects",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Remove references to unused objects",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "It’s possible for an app to accumulate memory that it has allocated and has access",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "to but doesn’t use. This unused memory increases the app’s memory use without contributing",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "to its functionality, and without showing up in leak-detection tools like the Leaks",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "instrument.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "For example, a social media app might load a list of messages from a service and",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "store them in a dictionary by message identifier. As the user scrolls through their",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "timeline, the app loads more messages into the dictionary so that it can quickly",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "display more information when the user taps a message. Without a strategy to purge",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "earlier messages from this dictionary, it can grow without bounds as the user scrolls",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "further along the list.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Make sure your app only keeps references to objects it needs to support the features",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "that the user is currently working with. Discard old content, or write it to disk",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "for later retrieval. For example, the social media app can discard messages from",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "its dictionary when the user scrolls away from those messages.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
